6





5151 Osage Beach PkwySte BOsage Beach, MO 65065


        (888) 438-2427
    






Terrible alternative to Satellite.  We changed from DirectTV...how stupid were we!  We have had Charter for 1 month now and they have been out 4 times already to try and fix their system.  All 4 times we had 4 different diagnosis.  One was that it was grounded wrong from installation, next was our cable in the house is old and needs to be replaced because our house is old.  Our house is 10 years old...i guess their definition of old is 10 years.  Third time back to grounding issue.  Fourth time finally had someone that had a clue.  The problem is not with our installation, wiring or age of our house.  It is their new program guide where they do not have all the bugs out yet.  Who knows when this will get fixed.

going back to DirectTV.  It's more expensive, but at least it works and has way more advantages.

If you are thinking of going to Charter/Spectum run fast...







Charter Internet works fine, but their customer service and the fact that they keep raising prices on loyal customers stinks. They will not even work with people who have been with them for 5 years. I have had two price increases and could stand no more. Their people are the worst and their constant calling trying to up-sale you is the pits. I would stay away from this company with a 10 foot pole, contact the attorney generals office and tell him you want a choice in providers and that you are tired of the monopolies created by cable/internet providers.







I went in to exchange a digital decoder box and get an M card and tuning adapter. After being told they didn't have either one the second girl pulled them out of the closet. I mentioned I need the USB cord for the tuning adapter and was promptly told they did not have one. After she disappeared in the back for 5 minutes returning with the cord, and now 5 customers deep behind me. She was unable to get the M Card or Tuning Adapter to scan into the computer so I was, of course, told they were bad and they would have to send a tech sometime next week. 

I don't live here full time so I left with nothing but a cavalier attitude of How they could care less about my cable problems. Come back next time you're down.

Charter has a reputation of crappy service here. You can not get a phone number so you can call this office location. You have to drive all the way over there, no matter where you are, so you can find out they can't help you.

Subsequent to this visit the 800# told me they have plenty of M cards on hand. I stayed an extra day only to be told once again, "we don't have any".







The boxes to rent break down a lot. It's not worth "renting" the boxes for cable so they can make more money off people at the lake.  You can't even get HD on a new tv even if you have more than just the basic cable!.   Customer service is not well either.  They either don't know how to help, very slow or just don't care.    I rather go back to dish tv than pay money to "rent" a box each month so Charter can make extra money off all of us.     The lake NEEDS better and more cable companies.







This is the worse office I have ever visited. they have monopolized cable here at the lake.... so you don't have any choices...







Worst experience ever. Went in with questions regarding my bill and the sales associate said she only does sales and can't provide any help. Cs he was the one that set up the account and the billing information that was messed up to begin with. Horrible. Switching providers







