ShareOverviewSummaryCharter Communications Inc. and its subsidiaries have worked on eight hundred and sixty-two contracts worth $12.6 million USD in obligations from the federal government since FY2007. In its latest active fiscal year (2016), the organization received a total of $1.36 million USD in obligations.The principal agencies it has contracted with are the Department of Veterans Affairs, Department of Justice, and Department of Defense.

